Defendant Miguel A Rosas Gomes in court, in custody, with attorney Michael H. Kopp.   Timothy Suha appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Patrick Ryan appeared as interpreter.    The Defendant was sentenced to the following:

IMPOSED SENTENCE of: 

10 YEARS IMPRISONMENT (CREDIT - 103 days) - Commencing forthwith. 
  -  3 YEARS OF INITIAL CONFINEMENT
  -  7 YEARS OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION;

CONDITIONS OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION:  
*AODA Assessment and follow through with any treatment recommended;
*Absolute Sobriety;  Random U.A.'s ; 
*No Use or Possession of alcohol, controlled substances or drug paraphernalia.
*No Use or Possession of prescription drugs without a valid prescription;
*Follow through with any treatment and/or counseling recommended by Agent;
*Maintain full time employment and/or combination of schooling;
*Any other term deemed appropriate by agent;
*No contact with:  co-defendant Kevin Mendieta Ramirez;
*DNA sample to be provided if not yet previously done.
*No association with known drug users or dealers and no contact at any place where illegal drugs are purchased, used, stored, packaged, or distributed.
*Perform 100 Hours Community Service;

RESTITUTION:  $6500.00 to Waukesha Metro Drug Unit - (apply cash bail to be paid as a condition of extended supervision - restitution to be paid before costs or fines);

COURT COSTS:  $268.00 (apply cash bail);

DNA SURCHARGE:  $250.00  (apply cash bail and balance to be refunded to poster);

Defendant is eligible for Challenge Incarceration Program.
Defendant is not eligible for Substance Abuse Program.

Felony warnings, voting rights and firearms warnings given.
